FBIS3-51176 "drlat010_k_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 SOUTH AMERICA Argentina Internal Security Budget Allocations for 1994 Disclosed PY1301215694 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 1946 GMT 13 Jan 94 PY1301215694 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Buenos Aires, 13 Jan (NA) -- Budget allocations for internal security this year grew by approximately 169 million pesos with respect to the allocations for 1993. The figures are included in the budget that Congress approved for 1994. The following is a comparative table of the allocations for 1993 and 1994: ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |1993 |1994 |Difference | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Internal Security |1,214,990,500 |1,353,106,754 |138,116,254 | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |SIDE [Secretariat |159,922,000 |191,800,000 |31,878,000 | |for State Intelli-| | | | |gence] | | | | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- As for the security forces, the following are the figures provided for in the 1994 budget: ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Federal Police: |560,962,000 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Border Police: |325,121,000 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Prefecture: |254,789,000 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- If these figures are added to the Armed Forces allocations, the total amount destined to defense and internal security amounts to 3,582,091,408 pesos, which is equivalent to 8.96 percent of the 1994 budget.
